is the human race's sense of humour becoming extinct all we seem to hear about these days is rage road rage trolley rage cabin rage and often here we seem to get keyboard rage with people wearing there fingers out rushing to post a jibe or put down in reply to other's genuine questions even the so called humour these days is snide underhand attacks and genuine humour and joshing is seen as a violation what is going on i brought up four boys on my own and if i hadn't had a sense of humour we all would have gone mad i had my rages alright by god i did but i dissipated my anger through humour before i calmy dealt with the situation i never humiliated them but i called them some things when they were teenagers and today they fondly imitate me as i was then but they'd often have preferred the spankings they had when they were little to the tongue lashings i gave them but they were full of humour and without malice obviously and that practice has stood me in good stead to this day why don't you try it yes i think it is people are too serious and money minded to stop and have a natter and a laugh all theyu are thinking is where is the next pound coming from when folk were poor they were a lot happier Spanking Humour Similarities between the Bible and the Qur'an Russian joke Theory of conduct The nature of God in Western theology Columbine High School massacre Theodicy Fred Phelps God Emperor of Dune Slow Train Coming Only Fools and Horses American Psycho Slashdot subculture Aristotle Supernatural Paul Is Dead I'm Sorry I Haven't a Clue Numerology Coming of Age (TNG episode) Ranma __ characters Shaggy dog story Ayyavazhi mythology Summa Theologiae Joke Past teachings of Prem Rawat K' She Loves You Criticisms of Charismatic and Pentecostal belief AFI 100 Years series The Lion, the Witch and the Wardrobe The Amber Spyglass EastEnders The Young Ones (TV series) The Battle (TNG episode) Captain Thunderbolt The Ashlee Simpson Show Milton H. Erickson Charles Dickens Goodness and 